    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chest - Aorta"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Measurement of pediatric thoracic aorta on contrast-enhanced axial CT."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Level A: 1 cm below aortic arch",
        "Level B: 1 cm cranial to aortic root",
        "Level C: 1 cm cranial to dome of right hemidiaphragm",
        "Formulas (mm): A1 = (0.72 x age) + 11.55; A2 = (0.629 x age) + 9.54; B1 = (0.668 x age) + 13; B2 = (0.572 x age) + 9.56; C = (0.559 x age) + 8.44",
        "Regression charts plot mean with 95% confidence limits",
        "Reference: Fitzgerald SW, Donaldson JS, Poznanski AK. Pediatric thoracic aorta: Normal measurements determined with CT. Radiology 1987;165:667-669."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "url": "https://www.ohsu.edu/sites/default/files/2019-01/DRAD%20PNM%20aorta_meas_jose.JPG",
      "alt": "Levels A-C and measurement sites on thoracic aorta"
    },
