    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chest - Bronchi"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Normal bronchial measurements and visibility."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Bronchiectasis defined by bronchus-to-artery ratio >1.2 on chest radiographs (external diameters).",
        "Normal bronchi are not usually seen in the most peripheral 5-10 mm of lung on CT.",
        "References: Woodring JH. Pulmonary artery-bronchus ratios in patients with normal lungs, pulmonary vascular plethora, and congestive heart failure. Radiology 1991;179:115-22. Siegel MJ. Pediatric Body CT. 1999. p.101."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chest - Cardiothoracic Index"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Frontal chest radiograph at 72 inches during quiet breathing."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "ID = internal diameter of chest at level of right hemidiaphragm",
        "MRD = max perpendicular diameter from midline to right heart border",
        "MLD = max perpendicular diameter from midline to left heart border",
        "CT index = (MRD + MLD) / ID"
      ]
    },
